{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17500423","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17500423"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:13:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:13:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1644"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1644","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1644"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.01,0.01,0.29,0.67]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1644"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70460"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1644","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1644"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1644"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55924"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"165"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"851"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3142"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23640"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42358"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70460","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70460"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of weight gain and new purple-red markings on his abdomen. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He has recently become very enthusiastic about strengh training, and trains regularly at the gym five times per week and maintains a strict diet. He does not smoke or drink alcohol. He additionally complains of fatigue and muscle weakness. On examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 88/min and blood pressure 154/82 mmHg, compared to 118/74 mmHg one year ago. There is central adiposity with skin changes on his lower abdomen (Image). \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ehlers-Danlos syndrome","Hypothyroidism","Growth hormone excess","Anabolic steroid use","Cushing syndrome"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of Cushing syndrome including central weight gain despite maintaining exercise and diet, purple-red abdominal striae, fatigue, muscle weakness, and new hypertension. \u003Cstrong\u003ECushing syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is caused by chronic exposure to excess glucocorticoids, either from endogenous overproduction or exogenous medication use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEhlers-Danlos syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a group of inherited connective tissue disorders characterised by skin hyperextensibility, joint hypermobility, and tissue fragility. While it can cause skin changes, it would not explain the central weight gain, hypertension, or muscle weakness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause weight gain and fatigue but typically presents with dry skin, cold intolerance, and bradycardia rather than hypertension. It would not explain the rapid onset of purple-red striae.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGrowth hormone excess\u003C/strong\u003E (acromegaly) can cause soft tissue swelling and some weight gain, but typically presents with enlargement of hands, feet, and facial features. It would not cause the rapid development of purple-red striae or central adiposity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnabolic steroid use\u003C/strong\u003E can cause weight gain and muscle hypertrophy but typically causes skin changes like acne rather than striae. Users often report this use when specifically asked, and the pattern of fat distribution would be different.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe next step in management would be to confirm hypercortisolism through biochemical testing, starting with a 24-hour urinary free cortisol or overnight dexamethasone suppression test.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Rapid central weight gain without change in diet, medication, or exercise is commonly caused by hypercortisolaemia.","Purple-red abdominal striae, hypertension, and central adiposity are classic features of Cushing\u0027s syndrome."],"references":["Chaudhry HS, Singh G. Cushing Syndrome. [Updated 2020 Dec 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2021 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470218/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55924"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1644"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"1687"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"1687","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/1687"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/af1dd52f-462b-426a-a209-4414d2faa7ee.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/af1dd52f-462b-426a-a209-4414d2faa7ee.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55924","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55924"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T13:32:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-15T13:32:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1644"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70460"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/